  <description type="morphology">Stem hyalodermis variably present, absent especially in depauperate plants. Leaves
        erect-spreading wet or dry, mostly 1–1.6(–2) mm, margins narrowly recurved proximally,
        rarely distally 2-stratose, base not differentiated in shape or ovate.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Capsules mature late summer–fall.</description>
  <description type="morphology">Calcareous regions, seepy bluffs to moist, seepy ledges and cracks, moist soil along
        waterfalls, streams and rivers, limestone and calcareous rocks and sediments, cedar barrens
        (sandstone), forested and more exposed stations;</description>
  <description type="morphology">low to high elevations (0–1900 m);</description>
